HEADWORD: Helichrysum
<hw>Hel`i*chry"sum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., the
marigold, fr. Gr. <?/ a kind of plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of composite plants, with shining, commonly white or yellow, or
sometimes reddish, radiated involucres, which are often called
⟦ldquo⟧everlasting flowers.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
